{
  "texts": [
    "The ultimate goal of AI is to create computer programs that can solve problems in the world like humans and perform specific tasks (McCarthy, 2007).",
    "To achieve this goal, one must be able to use AI effectively.",
    "Effective use of AI is possible through effective communication with it and specialization of the commands and cues used when giving it a task (Eager & Brunton, 2023).",
    "When using AI tools, the process of creating and writing these commands and cues that lead to the most accurate, relevant, and precise results among the possible responses is defined as prompt engineering (Lo, 2023; Short & Short, 2023).",
    "Eager and Brunton (2023) stated that when interacting with dialog-based AI models, the goal and context of the desired content should be clearly and concisely defined, and guidance should be provided by adding the necessary instructions and parameters for the appropriate outcome."
  ]
}